  "prompt": "What universities does Sonic Automotive recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Sonic Automotive actively recruits new graduates from a variety of universities, particularly those with strong programs in business, marketing, automotive engineering, and related fields. While specific universities can vary, they often focus on institutions that have robust business schools or automotive programs.\n\nIn terms of majors, Sonic Automotive typically looks for candidates with degrees in:\n\n1. **Business Administration**\n2. **Marketing**\n3. **Finance**\n4. **Automotive Engineering or Technology**\n5. **Supply Chain Management**\n6. **Management**\n7. **Human Resources**\n\nAdditionally, they may also consider graduates from fields such as communications or information technology, depending on the specific roles available.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it would be beneficial to check Sonic Automotive\u2019s careers page or consult their recruiting team for details on partnerships with specific universities and desired majors.",
